    "ref_entries": {
        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "described five different skin manifestations of COVID-19 in a large cohort of Spanish patients: pseudochilblain, vesicular eruptions, urticarial lesions, maculopapular eruptions and livedo or necrosis. Recently, a previously unreported pattern with erythema multiforme-like lesions was observed by Jimenez-Cauhe et al. 4 in four hospitalized patients diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia. Here we report a case of this peculiar skin condition as the inaugural manifestation of COVID-19 infection.",
            "latex": null,
            "type": "figure"
        },
        "FIGREF1": {
            "text": "dermatologists, we have to promote among other specialists the potential recognition of the possible cutaneous presentations of COVID-19, including uncommon manifestations, and lead to think about testing and/or re-testing COVID-19. Author contribution Statement: Luigi Gargiulo collected the clinical data, wrote the draft of the manuscript, adapted the clinical image and reviewed the manuscript. Giulia Pavia, Paola Facheris and Mario Valenti collected the clinical data and wrote a draft of the manuscript. Francesco Sacrini, Alessandra Narcisi, Riccardo Borroni and Antonio Costanzo collected the clinical data and critically reviewed the manuscript. Luca Livio Mancini collected clinical data, obtained the figures and critically reviewed the manuscript. All authors provided critical feedback and helped shape the manuscript.",
